snippet.textDisplay: It’s cool to see a channel like this so popular and thriving. I collected bugs when I was a kid and had a box to put them in. They were dead bugs and I didn’t intentionally kill any to put in there. I found lots of dragon flys and even found a dead caterpillar. That was a rare find. I live in Utah so bugs tend to be less colorful here, making caterpillars so hard to find. I liked ants but couldn’t put them in because they were too small. There were black ants everywhere and I remember finding a big one. I forget what it’s called but it’s more than a few steps up from a worker ant. Keep doing your stuff because I really like it and a lot of people would agree. I have barely been on this channel, but it’s really cool. Keep posting!
